292
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:11,460
In a darkened land,

293
00:20:12,030 --> 00:20:13,800
He comes and goes,

294
00:20:14,190 --> 00:20:17,140
In black and white,

295
00:20:17,330 --> 00:20:18,990
He’ll pick you up,

296
00:20:19,180 --> 00:20:22,860
When you’re feeling down,

297
00:20:23,450 --> 00:20:25,310
The man with no heart,

298
00:20:25,470 --> 00:20:30,710
He runs this town...

299
00:20:31,620 --> 00:20:35,730
The Man with a Million Drugs,

300
00:20:35,940 --> 00:20:40,310
He’s the Man with a Million Drugs.

301
00:20:48,510 --> 00:20:50,670
Oye Figs!

302
00:20:51,540 --> 00:20:52,830
Sit...

303
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:55,180
Mishra!

304
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:57,830
How are you?

305
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:58,520
Same old.

306
00:21:05,010 --> 00:21:06,580
So...

307
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:09,710
Yeah so....

308
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:11,960
Last night was an experience, yeah?

309
00:21:13,050 --> 00:21:16,210
Yeah well, guess you could say that.

310
00:21:16,210 --> 00:21:19,520
I mean you and Jay really hit it off?

311
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:22,240
What? Are you crazy?

312
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:27,190
No. Anyway I wanted to know
if I could score some hash?

313
00:21:27,790 --> 00:21:29,900
Any chance I can get some... hash?

314
00:21:30,340 --> 00:21:33,810
Hash. Hash...

315
00:21:34,120 --> 00:21:35,880
Oh hash...

316
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:38,290
Do you have some?

317
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:40,990
Yes... certainly!

318
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:48,680
Hash. Hash...

319
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:01,810
Figs, looks like I’m out.

320
00:22:01,910 --> 00:22:04,520
You’re joking, right?

321
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:07,440
No, no, no, I’m serious.

322
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:11,560
Okay tell me, in the meantime...

323
00:22:12,050 --> 00:22:14,850
Could I interest you in some keta?

324
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:20,390
I just scored it from our good friends over at
the Government of India veterinary institute.

325
00:22:22,510 --> 00:22:23,840
But what’s this, man?

326
00:22:24,100 --> 00:22:26,290
Ketamine. Horse tranquilizer.

327
00:22:28,670 --> 00:22:32,620
Yeah, well...

328
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,350
No cream, man?

329
00:22:36,350 --> 00:22:36,900
No.

330
00:22:37,220 --> 00:22:40,390
Just check if you have any cream.

331
00:22:40,810 --> 00:22:42,570
M Cream.

332
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:46,600
M Cream, man.
The best hash in the world.

333
00:22:47,290 --> 00:22:49,050
One puff and nirvana.

334
00:22:49,370 --> 00:22:51,320
Sweet enough for Shiva himself.

335
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:55,720
It’s gone. It’s gone
my friend. It’s finished.

336
00:22:55,850 --> 00:22:58,270
It’s returned to the
pantheon of the destroyer.

337
00:23:01,910 --> 00:23:05,310
Alas. In that case
we mortals lie bereft.

338
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,880
This is a dire situation!

339
00:23:14,310 --> 00:23:17,260
And round and
round and round it goes.

340
00:23:18,850 --> 00:23:25,350
Life is a dream for the wise,
a game for the fool,

341
00:23:25,810 --> 00:23:32,500
a comedy for the rich,
a tragedy for the poor.

342
00:23:35,890 --> 00:23:37,660
Life, how does it matter anyway?

343
00:23:40,370 --> 00:23:42,090
It’s just a brothel.

344
00:23:43,340 --> 00:23:45,680
And round and
round and round it goes.

345
00:23:53,350 --> 00:23:56,540
Arun, get up! We have to
go for lunch to the Khots’.

346
00:23:56,930 --> 00:24:00,480
You know what they’re
like... sticky. Come on.

347
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:02,600
Oh dear. I’m ready, I’m ready.

348
00:24:14,780 --> 00:24:15,550
You know, Arun...

349
00:24:15,890 --> 00:24:17,990
I’ve been thinking,
we should take Figs with us.

350
00:24:18,280 --> 00:24:22,290
What the hell for? Let the young lad
do some work for a change.

351
00:24:23,450 --> 00:24:24,640
You remember Irina?

352
00:24:24,730 --> 00:24:25,600
Who?

353
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:27,370
Mr and Mrs Khots little girl.

354
00:24:27,910 --> 00:24:28,380
Ah.

355
00:24:28,570 --> 00:24:34,180
It just so happens she’s come back from
the US and she’s not so little anymore.

356
00:24:34,270 --> 00:24:34,950
Oh.

357
00:24:35,030 --> 00:24:38,440
I think she would make
a great match for Figs.

358
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,000
A very suitable couple.

359
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:43,530
But I thought young Figs was besotted
with, what’s her name, Maggie.

360
00:24:43,870 --> 00:24:45,480
Forget about Maggie.

361
00:24:49,020 --> 00:24:50,140
(Car Honk)

362
00:24:56,930 --> 00:24:58,370
(Car Honk)

363
00:24:58,750 --> 00:25:00,080
What was that noise?

364
00:25:03,020 --> 00:25:03,710
Figs!

365
00:25:05,210 --> 00:25:06,440
What’s going on?

366
00:25:06,660 --> 00:25:07,520
Hey guys.

367
00:25:08,170 --> 00:25:10,540
Where do you think you’re going?

368
00:25:10,860 --> 00:25:13,950
I’m just heading to the hills.
I’ll be gone for a few days.

369
00:25:14,130 --> 00:25:16,000
What? Why?

370
00:25:16,550 --> 00:25:17,320
Road trip.

371
00:25:17,390 --> 00:25:20,340
Road trip? What are you
talking about? Are you serious!

372
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:22,970
Yeah, I should have
told you this earlier but...

373
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:27,240
You know, this is all very
dramatic and awkward and stuff...

374
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:28,340
So I’m just going to take your leave.

375
00:25:28,390 --> 00:25:29,050
See you guys!

376
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:29,810
Figs!

377
00:25:31,290 --> 00:25:34,880
You’ve got to stop running if you really
want to find what you’re looking for.

378
00:25:41,250 --> 00:25:43,650
Arun! Do something!

379
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:46,770
Vandana! Do What?

380
00:25:46,870 --> 00:25:55,370
Yes I’ll be chasing all you to the street,

381
00:25:56,830 --> 00:26:01,510
I’ll be chasing; I’ll be racing,

382
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:06,630
You to the street,

383
00:26:07,950 --> 00:26:10,650
To the street...

384
00:26:11,890 --> 00:26:12,690
See you later!

385
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:15,040
Hello.

386
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:17,250
Hey! Come on. Let’s go, man.

387
00:26:17,710 --> 00:26:19,060
Whoa.

388
00:26:20,210 --> 00:26:22,370
Oh Figs. You’ve met Jay, right?

389
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:24,330
She went to school with Niz.

390
00:26:25,870 --> 00:26:27,070
Ah.

391
00:26:27,190 --> 00:26:27,810
Hi.

392
00:26:28,550 --> 00:26:29,640
You guys know each other?

393
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:35,700
No... Thankfully.

394
00:26:37,730 --> 00:26:38,400
Oh.

395
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,120
Oh.

396
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:47,030
Maggie, I didn’t know she was coming.

397
00:26:47,070 --> 00:26:48,050
Figs, relax, man.

398
00:26:48,310 --> 00:26:50,910
- So what’s the big deal?
- Maggie, man...

399
00:26:52,990 --> 00:26:55,650
I hope you have enough booze
at least. I just got one bottle with me.

400
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:56,850
Yeah. It’s at the back.

401
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:59,590
- Niz, can you just check?
- Yeah, yeah...

402
00:26:59,990 --> 00:27:01,310
At your service!

403
00:27:05,780 --> 00:27:08,770
So... Two bottles of vodka.

404
00:27:08,910 --> 00:27:14,290
Coke, vodka and more vodka.

405
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:16,470
Maggie?

406
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:18,190
What? I like vodka.

407
00:27:18,690 --> 00:27:19,680
No scotch?

408
00:27:20,010 --> 00:27:20,580
Nope.

409
00:27:21,410 --> 00:27:22,860
That must be corrected.

410
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:23,560
Yup.

411
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:27,120
Scotch? Alright.

412
00:27:27,830 --> 00:27:28,980
You drink scotch?

413
00:27:30,580 --> 00:27:31,140
Yes.

414
00:27:31,850 --> 00:27:35,110
That’s nice. Cool, me too.

415
00:27:36,630 --> 00:27:39,090
We’ll pick it up on the way. Come on...

416
00:27:39,110 --> 00:27:39,770
Let’s go.

417
00:27:39,850 --> 00:27:40,580
Getting late...

418
00:27:42,970 --> 00:27:43,810
Ready guys?

419
00:27:43,850 --> 00:27:45,850
- You’ll tell me later.
- Yeah I will.

420
00:27:47,290 --> 00:27:49,060
(Music)

421
00:27:53,310 --> 00:27:55,040
On the road again.

422
00:27:55,640 --> 00:28:01,210
None are more hopelessly enslaved than
those who falsely believe they are free.

423
00:28:03,420 --> 00:28:07,010
And there we were,
children of chaos and anarchy.

424
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:09,270
Escaping into the endless unknown.

425
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:11,820
We are free.

426
00:28:13,740 --> 00:28:14,910
On the road again.

427
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:21,070
Butter chicken and bread?

428
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:21,990
Sir, it’s over.

429
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:25,000
Okay.

430
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:28,060
Mughlai chicken and bread?

431
00:28:28,070 --> 00:28:28,830
Sir, it’s over.

432
00:28:29,740 --> 00:28:30,590
Is anything available?

433
00:28:30,630 --> 00:28:33,750
- Sir, you tell me!
- No you tell me!

434
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,010
Chicken fry...

435
00:28:35,300 --> 00:28:36,630
- And bread?
- Yes, sir.

436
00:28:36,650 --> 00:28:37,190
Done.

437
00:28:37,570 --> 00:28:39,420
With vegetables on the side.

438
00:28:39,450 --> 00:28:40,550
- Okay.
- Thank you.

439
00:28:41,610 --> 00:28:43,870
So where are we spending the night?

440
00:28:44,380 --> 00:28:47,400
Oh... At this abandoned guest
house just off the highway.

441
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:50,590
My uncle owns it, he’s a minister.

442
00:28:52,010 --> 00:28:53,080
Abandoned?

443
00:28:53,750 --> 00:28:58,730
Yeah. I think it used to be Indira Gandhi’s
guest house or something like that.

444
00:28:58,790 --> 00:29:01,280
But no one lives there anymore.

445
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:04,450
Haunted house.

446
00:29:04,570 --> 00:29:09,010
Shut up, Niz. Don’t kid around.

447
00:29:11,380 --> 00:29:12,690
I’m scared of ghosts.

448
00:29:12,750 --> 00:29:14,510
Yeah, ghosts are so scary.

449
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:16,880
Anyway screw that.

450
00:29:17,730 --> 00:29:19,890
Mababajagal here we come!

451
00:29:19,930 --> 00:29:23,160
I can smell the cream and it smells good.

452
00:29:23,580 --> 00:29:25,230
What is he talking about?

453
00:29:25,620 --> 00:29:26,870
We’re going to Dharamsala.

454
00:29:27,460 --> 00:29:30,220
What the hell is Mababajagal?

455
00:29:30,260 --> 00:29:31,410
Dharamsala?

456
00:29:32,820 --> 00:29:35,720
Er Jay, right...

457
00:29:38,310 --> 00:29:42,500
Mababajagal is this mythical magical place.

458
00:29:42,590 --> 00:29:45,860
The source of M Cream,
this mythical magical hash.

459
00:29:46,020 --> 00:29:48,770
And... we’re all going to go look for it.

460
00:29:49,150 --> 00:29:51,350
And Figs...

461
00:29:51,890 --> 00:29:54,880
We are going to Dharamsala first.

462
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,440
Jay and I’ve got an old friend there, Thupten.

463
00:29:57,840 --> 00:30:00,670
Plus she’s doing a write-up on Tibetans...

464
00:30:00,690 --> 00:30:01,560
...in exile...

465
00:30:01,570 --> 00:30:04,440
...and I’m taking photographs.

466
00:30:04,710 --> 00:30:06,590
Remember I told you?

467
00:30:06,720 --> 00:30:08,500
The assignment...

468
00:30:10,560 --> 00:30:11,450
What?

469
00:30:11,950 --> 00:30:13,780
What are you looking at me for?

470
00:30:15,540 --> 00:30:17,420
Will you grow up?

471
00:30:19,340 --> 00:30:19,840
Yeah...

472
00:30:20,060 --> 00:30:21,160
Maybe I will.

473
00:30:21,420 --> 00:30:23,920
When you stop being a
self-righteous, little bimbo!

474
00:30:24,840 --> 00:30:26,490
Dude, relax.

475
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:27,880
It’s not her fault.

476
00:30:30,890 --> 00:30:33,480
I think I’ve diagnosed
your problem, Figaro.

477
00:30:33,540 --> 00:30:34,390
Really, what is it?

478
00:30:34,910 --> 00:30:38,250
You’re just a spoilt, selfish brat...

479
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:40,930
...who thinks of nothing
other than his own petty existence.

480
00:30:41,350 --> 00:30:43,740
And you’re just a
hypocritical little bimbo.

481
00:30:43,790 --> 00:30:45,010
Hypocritical?

482
00:30:45,430 --> 00:30:46,160
Oh yeah?

483
00:30:47,130 --> 00:30:48,020
People like you...

484
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:50,660
...spout shit about this cause...

485
00:30:50,690 --> 00:30:51,450
...and that cause!

486
00:30:51,470 --> 00:30:52,100
And you sit here,

487
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:52,940
do nothing about it.

488
00:30:53,380 --> 00:30:55,660
It’s almost funny if it weren’t so pathetic.

489
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:58,430
I do what I do...

490
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:00,140
...because it affects me.

491
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:01,160
Okay?

492
00:31:01,680 --> 00:31:04,590
It affects me when there’s a
random terrorist attack in my city.

493
00:31:04,630 --> 00:31:08,910
It affects me when the government
goes on and on about our rising GDP...

494
00:31:08,930 --> 00:31:11,270
...when a majority of our
people are still poor.

495
00:31:11,290 --> 00:31:14,010
And it affects me that no
one gives a damn about Tibet.

496
00:31:14,030 --> 00:31:16,580
Because there’s no
oil there, there’s only people.

497
00:31:16,620 --> 00:31:18,760
It affects me so fuck you!

498
00:31:18,790 --> 00:31:19,920
It affects you?

499
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:21,580
Miss, I hate to say it...

500
00:31:22,300 --> 00:31:24,330
...but you’re a walking cliche.

501
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:26,770
Come on... Unbelievable.

502
00:31:30,930 --> 00:31:31,620
Figs.

503
00:31:32,670 --> 00:31:34,410
What’s your problem, man?

504
00:31:40,900 --> 00:31:41,910
Drama.

505
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:43,250
I love it.

506
00:31:44,150 --> 00:31:48,720
And for all those locks and keys,

507
00:31:48,750 --> 00:31:52,620
Yeah, we leave them all behind,

508
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:59,870
For the leaves and for the trees,

509
00:31:59,930 --> 00:32:03,640
For the countless lullabies.

510
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:04,390
Spooky.

511
00:32:05,380 --> 00:32:06,930
Shut up.

512
00:32:10,900 --> 00:32:14,400
Sleeping arrangements. Shotgun, Niz
and I will take the big bedroom.

513
00:32:14,910 --> 00:32:16,530
Jay, you can have the other one.

514
00:32:16,700 --> 00:32:20,590
- And Figs, the couch is all yours.
- Yay!

515
00:32:21,780 --> 00:32:23,530
Niz, make the drinks quickly!

516
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:24,420
That’s what I’m doing.

517
00:32:26,290 --> 00:32:28,990
Yuck! This place is so dirty.

518
00:32:29,250 --> 00:32:31,450
This place is beautiful.

519
00:32:34,490 --> 00:32:35,990
I am so exhausted.

520
00:32:38,610 --> 00:32:39,310
Here you go!

521
00:32:39,330 --> 00:32:40,450
Thank you.

522
00:32:42,580 --> 00:32:43,900
And here you go...

523
00:32:49,610 --> 00:32:51,870
A toast to us... a toast to us...

524
00:32:52,900 --> 00:33:00,090
...and to the dangerous promise
of the unknown road ahead.

525
00:33:02,390 --> 00:33:04,150
I’ll drink to that!

526
00:33:04,430 --> 00:33:05,170
Cheers.

527
00:33:14,120 --> 00:33:14,560
So...

528
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:18,130
Do you guys do these
road trip things often?

529
00:33:18,940 --> 00:33:19,470
You think?

530
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:24,500
Getting Niz to go someplace is like getting
Anna Hazare to clean up corruption.

531
00:33:25,260 --> 00:33:26,690
Easier said than done.

532
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:30,420
Well unlike some people
I have a earn a living.

533
00:33:30,700 --> 00:33:33,980
What you gonna’ do?
Working class blues...

534
00:33:34,590 --> 00:33:36,270
What’s with that attitude?

535
00:33:37,320 --> 00:33:37,970
Nothing...

536
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:45,820
It’s just that you seem to forget that...
we did go to Jim Corbett over winter break.

537
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:47,320
For, like, two days!

538
00:33:47,430 --> 00:33:51,490
And please that’s because Rishi was
going through this animal planet phase.

539
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:52,740
It doesn’t count.

540
00:33:52,840 --> 00:33:54,020
Who’s Rishi?

541
00:33:54,450 --> 00:33:58,970
Rishi Rastogi. We used
to hangout a lot, earlier...

542
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:04,410
He came out. Yeah...
